var.name: abstract
var.description: Abstract of the item (e.g. the abstract of a journal article)

var.name: annote
var.description: Short markup, decoration, or annotation to the item (e.g., to indicate items included in a review); For descriptive text (e.g., in an annotated bibliography), use note instead

var.name: archive
var.description: Archive storing the item

var.name: archive_collection
var.description: Collection the item is part of within an archive

var.name: archive_location
var.description: Storage location within an archive (e.g. a box and folder number)

var.name: archive-place
var.description: Geographic location of the archive

var.name: authority
var.description: Issuing or judicial authority (e.g. “USPTO” for a patent, “Fairfax Circuit Court” for a legal case)

var.name: call-number
var.description: Call number (to locate the item in a library)

var.name: citation-key
var.description: Identifier of the item in the input data file (analogous to BibTeX entrykey); Use this variable to facilitate conversion between word-processor and plain-text writing systems; For an identifer intended as formatted output label for a citation (e.g. “Ferr78”), use citation-label instead

var.name: citation-label
var.description: Label identifying the item in in-text citations of label styles (e.g. “Ferr78”); May be assigned by the CSL processor based on item metadata; For the identifier of the item in the input data file, use citation-key instead

var.name: collection-title
var.description: Title of the collection holding the item (e.g. the series title for a book; the lecture series title for a presentation)

var.name: container-title
var.description: Title of the container holding the item (e.g. the book title for a book chapter, the journal title for a journal article; the album title for a recording; the session title for multi-part presentation at a conference)

var.name: container-title-short
var.description: Short/abbreviated form of container-title; Deprecated; use variable="container-title" form="short" instead

var.name: dimensions
var.description: Physical (e.g. size) or temporal (e.g. running time) dimensions of the item

var.name: division
var.description: Minor subdivision of a court with a jurisdiction for a legal item

var.name: DOI
var.description: Digital Object Identifier (e.g. “10.1128/AEM.02591-07”)

var.name: event
var.description: Deprecated legacy variant of event-title

var.name: event-title
var.description: Name of the event related to the item (e.g. the conference name when citing a conference paper; the meeting where presentation was made)

var.name: event-place
var.description: Geographic location of the event related to the item (e.g. “Amsterdam, The Netherlands”)

var.name: genre
var.description: Type, class, or subtype of the item (e.g. “Doctoral dissertation” for a PhD thesis; “NIH Publication” for an NIH technical report); Do not use for topical descriptions or categories (e.g. “adventure” for an adventure movie)

var.name: ISBN
var.description: International Standard Book Number (e.g. “978-3-8474-1017-1”)

var.name: ISSN
var.description: International Standard Serial Number

var.name: jurisdiction
var.description: Geographic scope of relevance (e.g. “US” for a US patent; the court hearing a legal case)

var.name: keyword
var.description: Keyword(s) or tag(s) attached to the item

var.name: language
var.description: The language of the item; Should be entered as an ISO 639-1 two-letter language code (e.g. “en”, “zh”), optionally with a two-letter locale code (e.g. “de-DE”, “de-AT”)

var.name: license
var.description: The license information applicable to an item (e.g. the license an article or software is released under; the copyright information for an item; the classification status of a document)

var.name: medium
var.description: Description of the item’s format or medium (e.g. “CD”, “DVD”, “Album”, etc.)

var.name: note
var.description: Descriptive text or notes about an item (e.g. in an annotated bibliography)

var.name: original-publisher
var.description: Original publisher, for items that have been republished by a different publisher

var.name: original-publisher-place
var.description: Geographic location of the original publisher (e.g. “London, UK”)

var.name: original-title
var.description: Title of the original version (e.g. “Война и мир”, the untranslated Russian title of “War and Peace”)

var.name: part-title
var.description: Title of the specific part of an item being cited

var.name: PMCID
var.description: PubMed Central reference number

var.name: PMID
var.description: PubMed reference number

var.name: publisher-place
var.description: Geographic location of the publisher

var.name: references
var.description: Resources related to the procedural history of a legal case or legislation; Can also be used to refer to the procedural history of other items (e.g. “Conference canceled” for a presentation accepted as a conference that was subsequently canceled; details of a retraction or correction notice)

var.name: reviewed-genre
var.description: Type of the item being reviewed by the current item (e.g. book, film)

var.name: reviewed-title
var.description: Title of the item reviewed by the current item

var.name: scale
var.description: Scale of e.g. a map or model

var.name: source
var.description: Source from whence the item originates (e.g. a library catalog or database)

var.name: status
var.description: Publication status of the item (e.g. “forthcoming”; “in press”; “advance online publication”; “retracted”)

var.name: title
var.description: Primary title of the item

var.name: title-short
var.description: Short/abbreviated form of title; Deprecated; use variable="title" form="short" instead

var.name: URL
var.description: Uniform Resource Locator (e.g. “https://aem.asm.org/cgi/content/full/74/9/2766”)

var.name: volume-title
var.description: Title of the volume of the item or container holding the item; Also use for titles of periodical special issues, special sections, and the like

var.name: year-suffix
var.description: Disambiguating year suffix in author-date styles (e.g. “a” in “Doe, 1999a”)

var.name: chapter-number
var.description: Chapter number (e.g. chapter number in a book; track number on an album)

var.name: citation-number
var.description: Index (starting at 1) of the cited reference in the bibliography (generated by the CSL processor)

var.name: collection-number
var.description: Number identifying the collection holding the item (e.g. the series number for a book)

var.name: edition
var.description: (Container) edition holding the item (e.g. “3” when citing a chapter in the third edition of a book)

var.name: first-reference-note-number
var.description: Number of a preceding note containing the first reference to the item; Assigned by the CSL processor; Empty in non-note-based styles or when the item hasn’t been cited in any preceding notes in a document

var.name: issue
var.description: Issue number of the item or container holding the item (e.g. “5” when citing a journal article from journal volume 2, issue 5); Use volume-title for the title of the issue, if any

var.name: locator
var.description: A cite-specific pinpointer within the item (e.g. a page number within a book, or a volume in a multi-volume work); Must be accompanied in the input data by a label indicating the locator type (see the Locators term list), which determines which term is rendered by cs:label when the locator variable is selected.

var.name: number
var.description: Number identifying the item (e.g. a report number)

var.name: number-of-pages
var.description: Total number of pages of the cited item

var.name: number-of-volumes
var.description: Total number of volumes, used when citing multi-volume books and such

var.name: page
var.description: Range of pages the item (e.g. a journal article) covers in a container (e.g. a journal issue)

var.name: page-first
var.description: First page of the range of pages the item (e.g. a journal article) covers in a container (e.g. a journal issue)

var.name: part-number
var.description: Number of the specific part of the item being cited (e.g. part 2 of a journal article); Use part-title for the title of the part, if any

var.name: printing-number
var.description: Printing number of the item or container holding the item

var.name: section
var.description: Section of the item or container holding the item (e.g. “§2.0.1” for a law; “politics” for a newspaper article)

var.name: supplement-number
var.description: Supplement number of the item or container holding the item (e.g. for secondary legal items that are regularly updated between editions)

var.name: version
var.description: Version of the item (e.g. “2.0.9” for a software program)

var.name: volume
var.description: Volume number of the item (e.g. “2” when citing volume 2 of a book) or the container holding the item (e.g. “2” when citing a chapter from volume 2 of a book); Use volume-title for the title of the volume, if any

var.name: accessed
var.description: Date the item has been accessed

var.name: available-date
var.description: Date the item was initially available (e.g. the online publication date of a journal article before its formal publication date; the date a treaty was made available for signing)

var.name: event-date
var.description: Date the event related to an item took place

var.name: issued
var.description: Date the item was issued/published

var.name: original-date
var.description: Issue date of the original version

var.name: submitted
var.description: Date the item (e.g. a manuscript) was submitted for publication

var.name: chair
var.description: The person leading the session containing a presentation (e.g. the organizer of the container-title of a speech)

var.name: collection-editor
var.description: Editor of the collection holding the item (e.g. the series editor for a book)

var.name: compiler
var.description: Person compiling or selecting material for an item from the works of various persons or bodies (e.g. for an anthology)

var.name: composer
var.description: Composer (e.g. of a musical score)

var.name: container-author
var.description: Author of the container holding the item (e.g. the book author for a book chapter)

var.name: contributor
var.description: A minor contributor to the item; typically cited using “with” before the name when listed in a bibliography

var.name: curator
var.description: Curator of an exhibit or collection (e.g. in a museum)

var.name: director
var.description: Director (e.g. of a film)

var.name: editorial-director
var.description: Managing editor (“Directeur de la Publication” in French)

var.name: editor-translator
var.description: Combined editor and translator of a work; The citation processory must be automatically generate if editor and translator variables are identical; May also be provided directly in item data

var.name: executive-producer
var.description: Executive producer (e.g. of a television series)

var.name: guest
var.description: Guest (e.g. on a TV show or podcast)

var.name: host
var.description: Host (e.g. of a TV show or podcast)

var.name: illustrator
var.description: Illustrator (e.g. of a children’s book or graphic novel)

var.name: interviewer
var.description: Interviewer (e.g. of an interview)

var.name: narrator
var.description: Narrator (e.g. of an audio book)

var.name: organizer
var.description: Organizer of an event (e.g. organizer of a workshop or conference)

var.name: original-author
var.description: The original creator of a work (e.g. the form of the author name listed on the original version of a book; the historical author of a work; the original songwriter or performer for a musical piece; the original developer or programmer for a piece of software; the original author of an adapted work such as a book adapted into a screenplay)

var.name: performer
var.description: Performer of an item (e.g. an actor appearing in a film; a muscian performing a piece of music)

var.name: producer
var.description: Producer (e.g. of a television or radio broadcast)

var.name: recipient
var.description: Recipient (e.g. of a letter)

var.name: reviewed-author
var.description: Author of the item reviewed by the current item

var.name: script-writer
var.description: Writer of a script or screenplay (e.g. of a film)

var.name: series-creator
var.description: Creator of a series (e.g. of a television series)
